cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SD, cs.CY 

This paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning techniques for classification. The focus is on cue phrases and their classification as discourse or sentential. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also uses machine learning algorithms, which suggests that it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also deals with data analysis and linguistic insights, which could place it in cs.SD (Sound and Data) or cs.CY (Computers and Society).
